          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cream, mix, roll",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C fan and line two baking trays. Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} and the first 200 g of {{caster-sugar}} until pale and creamed; this takes 2 to 3 minutes by hand. Beat in the {{eggs}} and {{vanilla-extract}}. Sift in the {{plain-flour}}, {{cream-of-tartar}} (the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "tang ingredient",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp99d2rc00000cv426rm4qeb"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": "), {{bicarbonate-of-soda}} and {{sea-salt-fine}} and mix to a soft dough. Mix the remaining {{caster-sugar}} with the {{cinnamon-ground}} in a shallow bowl. Roll the dough into 20 walnut-sized balls and toss each in the cinnamon sugar to coat fully.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 8 to 10 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Set the balls on the trays with 4 cm between each. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes; the biscuits should puff up and crack on top, then settle. The edges should be set, the centres still soft. Cool 5 minutes on the tray, then transfer to a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
